 * [[International Physicians for the Prevention of Nuclear War]], had affiliates in 41 nations in 1985, representing 135,000 physicians;<ref name=Wit164/> IPPNW was awarded the [[UNESCO]] [[UNESCO Prize for Peace Education|Peace Education Prize]] in 1984 and the [[Nobel Peace Prize]] in 1985.<ref>[http://www.ippnw.org/About/NobelHelix.html Profile from Helix Magazine] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091013120257/http://www.ippnw.org/About/NobelHelix.html |date=2009-10-13 }}</ref> * [[Nuclear Free World Policy]] * [[Nuclear Information and Resource Service]] * [[OPANAL]] * [[Parliamentarians for Nuclear Non-Proliferation and Disarmament]], global network of over 700 parliamentarians from more than 75 countries working to prevent nuclear proliferation.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newsday.co.zw/article/2011-10-17-coltart-elected-antinuclear-organisation-president |title=Coltart elected anti-nuclear organisation president |author=Henry Mhara |date=Oct 17, 2011 |work=News Day }}</ref> * [[Pax Christi International]], [[Catholic]] group which took a "sharply anti-nuclear stand".<ref name=Wit164>Lawrence S. Wittner (2009). ''Confronting the Bomb: A Short History of the World Nuclear Disarmament Movement'', Stanford University Press, pp. 164-165.</ref> * [[Ploughshares Fund]] * [[Pugwash Conferences on Science and World Affairs]] * [[Socialist International]], world body of social democratic parties.<ref name=Wit128/> * [[Sōka Gakkai]], a peace-orientated [[Buddhist]] organisation, which held anti-nuclear exhibitions in Japanese cities during the late 1970s, and gathered 10 million signatures on petitions calling for the abolition of nuclear weapons.<ref name=Wit128>Lawrence S. Wittner (2009). ''Confronting the Bomb: A Short History of the World Nuclear Disarmament Movement'', Stanford University Press, p. 128.</ref><ref name=Wit125>Lawrence S. Wittner (2009). ''Confronting the Bomb: A Short History of the World Nuclear Disarmament Movement'', Stanford University Press, p. 125.</ref> * [[The Ribbon International]], United Nations Non-Governmental Organization promoting [[nuclear disarmament]]. * [[United Nations Office for Disarmament Affairs]] * [[Fenner Brockway, Baron Brockway|World Disarmament Campaign]]<ref name=Wit128/> * [[World Information Service on Energy]], based in Amsterdam, The Netherlands * [[World Union for Protection of Life]]
