{{Infobox language |name=Cahuarano |nativename= |states=[[Perú]] |extinct=ca. 1990 |ref=e18 |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Zaparoan languages|Zaparoan]] |fam2=Iquito–Cahuarano |iso3=cah |glotto=cahu1268 |glottorefname=Cahuarano }}
'''Cahuarano''' is a recently extinct indigenous American language of the Zaparoan family, once spoken along the Nanay river in Peru. The last speaker died in the late 1980s or early 1990s.
