The '''Kusasi people''' (var. '''Kusaasi''') are an [[ethnic group]] in northern [[Ghana]] and southern [[Burkina Faso]]. They speak [[Kusaal language|Kusaal]], a [[Gur language]].<ref>[http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=kus Kusaal language]. Ethnologue.com.</ref>

==Festival==
The Kusasi people celebrate the '''[[Samanpiid Festival]]'''.<ref name=raw>{{cite web|title=Rawlings calls for cabinet reshuffle|url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/artikel.php?ID=296513|publisher=www.ghanaweb.com|accessdate=30 December 2013}}</ref> The festival is one that is used to thank God for a bumper harvest during the farming season.<ref name=raw/><ref name="omp">{{cite web | url=http://myjoyonline.com/politics/2013/December-30th/mahamas-appointees-not-correct-rawlings.php | title=Mahama's appointees not correct - Rawlings | publisher=myjoyonline.com | accessdate=30 December 2013}}</ref> The festival was first celebrated in 1987.<ref name="omp"/>

