'''Mythic Journeys''' is a performance festival and conference gathering held in [[Atlanta]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]], United States. Founded in 2004, it began as a celebration of the works of [[Joseph Campbell]] and has expanded into a celebration of the role of [[mythology|myth]] and [[storytelling]] in the modern world.
Organized by the [[Mythic Imagination Institute]], the conference attracts such guests as [[Deepak Chopra]], [[James Hillman]], [[Robert Bly]], [[Janis Ian]], [[John and Caitlin Matthews]], [[Wendy Froud|Wendy]] and [[Brian Froud]], [[Joyce Carol Oates]], [[Terri Windling]], Ulla Suokko,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ullasuokko.com/articles.htm |title=Watering the Jasmines |date= 2000-07-23 |work= }}</ref> and many other participants from such fields as psychology, religion, science, literature, education, entertainment, and the arts.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mytholog.com/reviews/mann_mythicjourneys.html |title=Mythic Journeys '06: Magic In Atlanta |date= 2000-07-18 |work= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.scifidimensions.com/Jun04/mythicjourneys.htm |title=Sci-Fi Dimensions Conference Report |date=2000-07-18 |work= |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040622021942/http://www.scifidimensions.com/Jun04/mythicjourneys.htm |archivedate=2004-06-22 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nethercraft.com/the_atlanta_journal-constitution_2004.html |title=A Modern-Day Journey |date= 2000-07-23 |work= |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070717160031/http://www.nethercraft.com/the_atlanta_journal-constitution_2004.html |archivedate=July 17, 2007 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theonering.net/torwp/2004/06/07/24733-ringer-review-of-mythic-journeys/ |title=Ringer Review of Mythic Journeys |date= 2000-07-23 |format= |work= }}</ref>
==''Mythic Journeys'' documentary== Released in 2009, the documentary film ''Mythic Journeys'' was written and directed by [[Steven Boe|Stephen]] and [[Whitney Boe]]. With footage taken from the 2006 Mythic Journeys festival,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.imaginalcellsinc.com/mythicjourneystrailer.htm |title=Mythic Journeys |publisher=Imaginal Cells Filmworks |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111125005110/http://www.imaginalcellsinc.com/mythicjourneystrailer.htm |archivedate=2011-11-25 |df= }}</ref> the movie includes animation and short film segments about the role of mythology & mysticism in modern society and storytelling, featuring interviews with [[Deepak Chopra]] and [[Michael Beckwith]]. Documentary footage is placed within a [[frame story]] for which [[Brian Froud|Brian]] and [[Wendy Froud]] created the puppets<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.worldoffroud.com/films/mythicjourneys.php |title=Mythic Journeys |publisher=World of Froud}}</ref> and actors [[Mark Hamill]], [[Lance Henriksen]], and [[Tim Curry]] provided the voices.
