'''Rind''' ({{Lang-bal|رِند}}) are a [[Baloch people|Baloch]] tribe settled in the [[Balochistan (Iran)|Balochistan province of Iran]], and the [[Balochistan (Pakistan)|Balochistan]], [[Sindh]] and [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]] provinces of [[Pakistan]].{{citation needed|date=September 2015}} According to Baloch folklore the tribe was founded by Rind, one of [[Mir Jalal Khan]]'s four sons.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Spooner|first1=Brian|title=BALUCHISTAN i. Geography, History and Ethnography|url=http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/baluchistan-i|website=[[Encyclopedia Iranica]]|accessdate=4 September 2015}}</ref> At the turn of the 15th century the Rind led by [[Mir Chakar Rind]] are believed to have engaged in a 30-year war against the Lashari, in which the Lashari were mostly wiped out. These events are the subject of many Balochi heroic [[ballads]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Elfenbein|first1=J.|title=BALUCHISTAN iii. Baluchi Language and Literature|url=http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/baluchistan-iii|website=[[Encyclopedia Iranica]]|accessdate=4 September 2015}}</ref>

